06/02/2022,748.2301(c) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/24/2022,08/24/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,Yes,"5 of the 7 children interviewed described negative interactions with staff such as being called demeaning names, being treated unfairly, and staff assuming children are misbehaving. ","On 7/22/22 an extension was granted due to the operation needing more time to complete face to face training with staff. The compliance was extended until 8/24/22 so the operation can have all current employees trained. LPerkins

On 8/24/22, an email from the administrator was received and the follow up plan was stated: Since this investigation was completed, three of Bridge to Hopes House Parents have resigned. Remaining staff and new hires received an additional training on 8/19/22, titled Power of Words and Positive Parenting. The training log with details will be uploaded to digital storage. 
As well, staff will receive on-going training specific to administering disciplinary measures in a positive way and focusing on learning from the situation. It is understood that children in our care do not always know why some behaviors are unacceptable and in addition to simply implementing consequences for behavioral issues staff should also be offering guidance. Being harsh or demeaning to children is not acceptable as a form of discipline. 
"
